---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Law Enforcement Officers | PoliceConduct.org"
  pagePath="/partner/law-enforcement-officer/"
>
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">
              Law Enforcement Officer
            </li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">The Officer's Integrity Vault</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Your career, your data, your shield.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Individual law enforcement officers
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  2026 brings higher scrutiny, deepfake risks, and reduced legal
                  protections.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">
              1. The 2026 problem: the wandering officer stigma
            </h2>
            <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3 mt-3">
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The career trap
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  New state laws mean a single administrative finding can follow
                  you forever. If an agency record is inaccurate, you could be
                  decertified without a personal way to dispute it.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The lateral hurdle
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Agencies are offering $50,000 sign-on bonuses for laterals,
                  but background processes are more invasive than ever.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The liability gap
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Personal professional liability insurance is no longer
                  optional. Defense costs for an administrative hearing now
                  average $15,000 to $40,000 out of pocket.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Ownership over oversight
                </div>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Control</span>
                    <span>Own your professional record across agencies.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Speed</span>
                    <span
                      >Shorten lateral hiring timelines with verified data.</span
                    >
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Privacy</span>
                    <span>Protect wellness data from unwanted disclosure.</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Our solution: a personal professional portfolio
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          policeconduct.org provides a CJIS-compliant digital vault that you
          control, even if you change departments.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  A. The narrative shield
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Defense against false claims</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Lock verified BWC metadata and CAD entries to counter edited
                    or false videos.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Claim your profile and add officer responses to
                    user-submitted reports.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Track your own commendation-to-complaint ratios and stress
                    flags.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  B. The $50k passport
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Career mobility</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Portable POST credits, specialized training, and awards in
                    one vault.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Grant temporary, view-only access to new agencies to cut
                    hiring time in half.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  C. Confined wellness
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Privacy-first support</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Anonymous wellness tracking with cumulative trauma exposure
                    insights.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Alerts go to the officer, not the chief, to enable early
                    self-intervention.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          3. Direct benefits for the rank and file
        </h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">The officer's pain point</th>
                <th scope="col">How policeconduct.org solves it</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>I'm one viral video from being fired.</td>
                <td>Verified data trails show total context of an encounter.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>I'm drowning in IA paperwork.</td>
                <td
                  >Automated reporting fills most use-of-force fields via
                  voice-to-text.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>I cannot afford a lawyer.</td>
                <td
                  >High-integrity profiles can lower liability insurance
                  premiums.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>I do not want the chief to know I am stressed.</td>
                <td
                  >Confidential wellness tracking shielded from fitness-for-duty
                  reviews.</td
                >
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">4. Why this matters to the union</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              Unions can protect members from administrative ambush by ensuring
              the data used to judge officers is accurate, complete, and
              includes commendations along with complaints.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Suggested next step
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Want a union support letter that explains why this system is a
                  shield for careers and not a snitch for the department?
                </p>
                <a
                  class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
                  href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20an%20Officer%20Integrity%20Vault%20union%20support%20letter."
                >
                  Request the union support letter
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
